I still cannot process how I landed a @iheartradio x @onfrolic podcast that is @lovestruckdaily! But I had a remarkably fun time being on it! Talking to Alisha and Sarah about my process, love and dating felt like having a chat with my girlfriends who I’d always known. Do give this one a listen! It’s super fun, and boys… there’s a special treat for you in there! Lol. (Link in bio)
.
.
Posted @withregram • @lovestruckdaily Who knows more about love than a poet? In the second part of our poetry series, we welcome contemporary confessional poet Shrutee Choudhary. We discuss all things language & love, and she even reads some of her beautiful poems to us. And for any sweet poetry nerds out there looking to make a couplet…she’s single, folks!

A few months ago, @rishabsmusic and I, along with a couple of other poets, started doing these rooms on @clubhouse where he’d play his soulful music while we’d perform our heartfelt pieces. 

Did we ever anticipate the amount of love we received? Or that a few months from then, we’d actually end up performing in front of a live audience IRL? Absolutely not. But life has a funny way of unravelling itself, and I’m in constant awe. 

Here’s to lifelong bonds and creative connections. Thank you @tejdeep.gill for recording this moment! And of course, Rishab, for giving me a spot on his wonderful, one of a kind tour! 

#sitarformentalhealth

latestIgtvVideos.title: Women’s Day
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here’s a little something I did with @monet_filmyzaade, with a piece that is really close to my heart. To all the incredible women I know! Happy every day.

-
This is for the women 
who get called bold 
more often when they are
bikini clad on the beach
carefree
than when they take 
a stance and raise
their voices against
abuse or harassment
or years of marital rape

This is for the women 
who excel at being 
photographers and writers
and engineers and doctors
but don’t get recognised
because they don’t 
upload their pictures often
or brag about 
their achievements

This is for the women 
who return from 
work only to manage
a messy house and cook
when the husbands
sit in front of television sets
watching the news
because they are too tired
to actually help

This is for the women
who just have to deal with
penetrating gazes
no matter what they wear
because “that’s just how 
men are”

This is for the women
who are independent enough
to live on their own
but get judged by the society
and are called names
if ever a man friend visits

For all the women
who have abortions 
in silence
go through inexplicable 
amount of pain all alone
because their fathers 
are too full of pride
to hold their daughters’ hand
because what will the society say?

For the women
who have to battle
their own families 
to free 
their own freedom

For the women
who think it’s okay
to compromise a little
in order to avoid messy 
situations

In your endurance
you’re brave

And I see you
we see you
we are your neighbours
your sisters, your daughters, your friends

And we applaud
your strength

We are a marvel
alone and together
with or without men
365 days a year 

Thought you should know.

We’ve been quietly building something special.

My mother has spent years teaching with heart, pouring her energy into shaping minds, sparking creativity, and nurturing confidence in everyone she meets.

Now, she’s bringing that passion into a space of her own—
And I’m helping bring it to life.

Introducing Hunar Kala – Ranchi’s very own creative hub.
An Arts & Skill Development Centre that offers everything from hand-painted saree workshops and tie-dye classes to acting, dance, creative writing, and soft skills training.

It’s a space where creativity isn’t just explored—it’s transformed into a skill you can grow, share, and even earn from.
A space for all ages, all dreams, and every kind of curious learner.

If you’re in Ranchi (or know someone who is), we’d love your support, your presence, or even just a kind word to help us begin this new journey.

Follow us or drop us a message to learn more about upcoming classes and workshops.

I cannot express in words, the gratitude I hold for my readers, my family and my friends. None of this would’ve been possible without you. 

A Garage Sale of Lovelorn Things is a collection of a hundred poems. It is metaphorical in its truest sense and the journey of writing it has helped me heal, let go and move on. Now, it’s time for me to let go of a piece of myself in the form of this book, for you to carry along.

You can buy copies on @amazondotin, @amazon, @flipkart, @amazonkindle, @becomeshakespeare etc., it’s live worldwide! It’d mean the world to me if you do. Like, share, comment and spread the word! I need your support now more than ever. 

With this book, I hope you’re able to break free from things that hold you back, feelings that weigh you down, and eventually make space for better things to come. 

You can also let me know in the comments what you’d like to let go of.

#letgoofyourheartbreak 
#agaragesaleoflovelornthings 

Cover design and illustrations: My heart, @prachimehta.co without whom this book would’ve never come to life. I love you.

And lastly, thank you @becomeshakespeare for giving my scattered feelings a home.

The in-betweenness of feeling and naming. 

I wanted to explore that emotion — the one that quietly weighs on your chest but hasn’t yet found the words to be born. The kind that lingers in glances, in stillness, in shared space, but hasn’t been incubated enough to be delivered into speech.

Its presence is undeniable, loud in its quiet, and holding it feels both beautiful and frustrating. Exciting. Disorienting. But the longer you hold it, the deeper it grows.

There’s a kind of quiet enrichment in that in-betweenness is an experience in itself,
one that deserves to be noticed,
to be valued.

Because it is that rare, to witness love in its becoming. 

Save this or better yet, send it to them to say it quietly. 🤍
